The '''Muon Gold''' was a [[Lubricant/Legends|lubricant]]-based [[Spice/Legends|spice]] that gave the user intensified mental clarity and focus for a short time. However, due to its eventual [[Alcohol/Legends|degrading effect]] on neural pathways, it was banned by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. It was therefore smuggled heavily and taken as a cheap drug.

The Muon Gold was the favorite spice of the [[Commerce Raiders|Bestine Pirates]]. These pirates were present in the [[Tatoo system/Legends|Tatoo system]] and named the region of space they inhabited, the [[Pirate's Gold]], after the spice.<ref name="SWG:PMG">{{SWGcite|exp=JtL|type=space_poi|Pirate's (Muon) Gold|Tatoo system}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Muon Gold appeared in the video game ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Star Wars video games#Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online role-playing game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]], prior to its closure on [[December 15]], 2011.

